gencastor (3.4-0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed bug for associations 1 to 1 that had no name on one side.
  * Added -c flag for generating code so that one can generate code outside
    the castor namespace
  * modified accordingly the use of namespaces, having in mind that some
    files are no more using the castor namespace by default

 -- Sebastien Ponce <sebastien.ponce@cern.ch>  Mon,  5 Sep 2005 11:00:00 +0200

gencastor (3.3-0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added generic Database cnv generator. This can work with databases
    supported by the abstract CDBC (Castor DataBase Connectivity) API.
    Oracle is already 100% supported but the oracle specific generator is
    still kept for production.

 -- Giuseppe Lo Presti <giuseppe.lopresti@cern.ch>  Mon, 24 Ago 2005 18:00:00 +0200

gencastor (3.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed C interfaces generation, only classes and interfaces are
    considered structs for the C world.
  * Fixed name of conversion svc, now is DbCnvSvc everywhere.
  * Fixed calls to commit() and rollback().

